Definition: having or demonstrating ability to recognize or draw fine distinctions
Example: an acute observer of politics and politicians; incisive comments; icy knifelike reasoning; as sharp and incisive as the stroke of a fang; penetrating insight; frequent penetrative observations
Synonyms: noun, cognition, acuteness, discriminating, incisive, attribute, incisiveness, keen, keenness, knifelike, penetrating, penetrative, verb, penetrate, piercing, sharp, sharpness, having, or, demonstrating, ability, to, recognize, draw, fine, distinctions, an, observer, of, politics, and, politicians, comments, icy, reasoning, as, the, stroke, a, fang, insight, frequent, observations
Category: adj.all
